And now for something a little different. 🎪⭐️🎪 Last Sunday we put on a “work in progress” show at cirque school. Every Sunday for the past 6 weeks we came together and got to experiment on an apparatus we’ve never worked on for a short period of time. While I’ve been working on static trapeze for many years. This experience was entirely new. And in the spirt if things being “work in progress” this was essentially a full improv to music. I hope I get to explore this a bit more in the new year. Thank you @CirqueSchool for always inspiring and @jimharmondirect for filming. #circus #wip #worktodo

Process. Rough concept to final. 🎨 While we wait for the next reveal, how about a different kind of sneak peek? Here’s a look behind my process on arriving at my final Hercules illustration for Epcot’s International Festival of the Arts. 👀🎨 Swipe to see. My very 1st rough thumbnail sketch scribbled out so I can see composition without wasting too much time. Second- My rough pass to see if it’s actually going to work. Third - clean up. This took forever as I wanted to also recreate the thick and thin line we used in the film. And finally my color illustration. Hope to see you in Florida when this piece debuts on January 13th! 🎨💪🏻🏺 #artfulepcot #epcot #disneyworld #fota #festivalofthearts #sthompsonart

Process. Rough concept to final. 🎨 While we wait for the next and final reveal, here’s a look behind my process on arriving at my final Hunchback of Norte Dame illustration for Epcot’s International Festival of the Arts. 👀🎨 Swipe to see more including the dates and times I’ll be at the festival. In order- Rough, clean up and final illustration. 🎨 I used a different clean up line here than the Hercules piece. In production of the film we used a very thin, feathery clean up line using a 0.3 mechanical pencil. I tried to recreate that here as well. ✍🏻 Hope to see you in Florida when this piece debuts on January 13th! 🎨🔔 #artfulepcot #epcot #disneyworld #fota #festivalofthearts #sthompsonart #hunchbackofnotredame

social_posts.post_text: Swipe for concept and details. New year, new merch! This 13” tall light up Tinker Bell collectible fig I designed is available now @shopdisney 💚 #peterpan #disney #tinkerbell #collectibles

Getting through the week like….💫💥🌈💖💪🏻 Lots of fun stuff coming up. And, I can’t believe Festival of the Arts starts next week. 👀 #disney #sthompsonart 🎨

Now available @shopdisney 👀 Yes. I also design dolls! What’s that? A brand new ILY doll collection from @shopdisney ! I get to work on a lot of projects. But I’m incredibly proud of these ladies. 
I was thrilled to be a part of the incredible design team that helped bring these new Disney dolls to life along with @court.watkinson @nonstopspiders @samanthacgeorge and @salty_bones Coming up with new characters that feel Disney in design, but are not actual characters was a fun challenge. Like the original ILY line, these are unique characters that are inspired by their favorite characters. I got to work through the design of the characters faces and body with our amazing sculptor Sean Pardell to make sure my drawings translated to 3D, then provide face deco overlays for our painter @thecheddahfactory to make sure everything looked just right. (Scroll for a few of my initial sketches and a closer look at the dolls.) Courtney did an amazing job working with the team on the parks theme, design of the outfits and accessories. Harmony, Sam and Jess then worked her magic to make sure everything came together looking fabulous. Thanks to our fearless leaders for an amazing opportunity and I hope you love these as much as we all do. Now, who’s your favorite? I can’t pick! #disney #shopdisney #ily4ever 
#ILY #dolls #dolldesign 💖🎨💖 For all the info you could want, head on over to shopdisney.com

Now she can be, part of your world. 🌊🧜🏽‍♀️🙌 Spotted at Disneyland and coming soon to a park near you. If she becomes available online, I will post about it. So keep an eye out. Swipe to see my original rough concept drawing and additional details. When I was asked to design a large collectible fig for Ariel, I knew exactly what I wanted to do. The sketch came in an instant. I wanted to capture the moment she decides to head towards the surface. But somehow really capture the feeling she is underwater. The pose, the hair and details had to be just right. You can almost feel her singing. I worked closely with our sculptor Sean Pardell who really knocked it out of the park. If you’re an Ariel fan, you’re going to want to pick this one up. And, the bronze Ursula fig that I designed is now available in full color to help create a perfect matching set! #ariel #partofyourworld #thelittlemermaid #mermaid #anditlightsup

And the photo shoots I’ve seen are all top notch. Being a part of the design team was a blast. And, we’re glad you’re liking them as much as we are. Thank you. 🙌 I just had to do a little sketch of our “inspired by Snow White” doll. #ily #disney #disneydolls #dolldesign #iloveyou4ever #disneyily4ever 🍎 available at @shopdisney @disneyparks and @target

Swipe for the full sketch. ✍🏻What’s that? You haven’t picked up our new Ily 4ever dolls at shop Disney? they’re available now @shopdisney @disneyparks and @target 👀 These were so fun to draw when we were busy working on them. So I pulled up an old sketch I did during development. It always helps to think of them as real characters instead of just a design. Here’s our “inspired by Belle and Tiana” girls. I wonder what they’re talking about? The design team did such an awesome job with these. Happy I got to be a part of it all. Which one is your favorite? #ily4ever #ilydolls #disney #dolldesign 💖

#TBT- Jem 💖 from one of my all time favorite cartoons from the 80s. Voiced by @samanthanewarkofficial , “Jem and the Holograms” The series revolves around Jerrica Benton, the owner and manager of Starlight Music, and as Jem, lead singer of the rock group The Holograms. Jerrica adopts the persona of Jem with the help of a holographic computer, known as Synergy, which was built by Jerrica's father to be "the ultimate audio-visual entertainment synthesizer" and is bequeathed to her after his death. Jerrica is able to command Synergy to project the hologram of Jem over herself by means of the remote micro-projectors in her earrings, thus disguising her features and clothing, enabling her to assume the Jem persona. Jem, through the use of her earrings, is also able to project holograms around her and uses this ability throughout the series to avoid danger and provide special effects for the performances of her group. And, it was AMAZING! One might say it was truly outrageous! 🙌💖🙌 #jem #jemandtheholograms #glitterandgold #jemstarearrings #starlightmusic #jerricabenton #showtimesynergy 💫⭐️💖 #trulyoutrageous

Just in time to celebrate #Disney100 💖 Our all-new, porcelain princess ornaments have found their way to the Disney Parks! 🙌 Each one comes in it’s own satin lined box. It was so much fun bringing these to life. We worked with our amazing sculptor Sean Pardell. The team worked tirelessly with the factory on the process of making molds, the sculpting process needed for porcelain, the different types of glaze, etc. All to make sure we made these the ultimate for princess collectors. Each individual ornament stands approximately 4.5” tall. ✨👑✨Get them while you can! #disneyprincess #porcelain #christmasornaments #porcilainprincess #collection update: Moana is available too! 🍥 check stories.

#ArtvsArtist2023 It’s that time again. Even after 29 years working with the Disney Company there are still new adventure’s to be had. I started out the year attending Epcot’s International Festival of the Arts for the first time! Then made my debut mid year with new art for the park galleries. And, heading back to Florida in a few weeks for a whole new batch of signings! All that while continuing to work on ornaments, collectibles and toys. Definitely one for the books. Let’s see what next year brings. #disney #artvsartist #disneyartist ✨🎨🙌

social_posts.post_text: Day 18 of #DISember. #GlenKeane 🎨 While we both worked in the same building for many years during my time in animation, I never had the opportunity to work with Glen until I started working on product. More specifically the Animators’ Collection dolls for @shopdisney 🎨 While we partnered with him on that project, we had time to talk about art, our careers and life in general. This drawing he did for me (and his pencil) are proudly framed in my home office. Thank you @glenkeaneprd for so many years of animation magic. The characters you helped create are a constant source of inspiration for my work. #disney #disneyartist

Sound on. So what exactly makes my “One of a Kind” art at Epcot this year one of a kind? While it is a canvas print of my digital art, I went back and reworked and hand painted about 85% of each piece. Hand painted backgrounds, added shadows and details not found in the other prints. Metallic paint, glitter paint, gems. And they’re hand signed! My intention was to stay as close to the original art from a distance, while tastefully adding a whole new layer and dimension to the artwork when viewed closely. And if that wasn’t enough, I worked directly with the framers and hand-picked each frame that I thought best represented each piece. you can find these in the Art of Disney Gallery in Epcot right now during the festival of the arts. Reminder that I am signing today through Saturday from 11 AM to 1 PM each day at the France pavilion. Hope to see you there. 🎨⭐️🎨 #artfulepcot #oneofakind #handembellished #waltdisneyworld 📷 thank you @missmindyart for capturing this little video. 😊

ART UPDATE!!! Ok. I’ve heard a strong rumor that Atlantis and Treasure Planet will be restocked later tonight or tomorrow (Saturday) morning. They will rejoin Tarzan and complete the trio. So, keep asking.  And keep a lookout. I have exactly one more signing tomorrow from 11-1pm in the France pavilion. See you there. 🎨🎨🎨

The absolute honor of a lifetime! To have my photo taken with the entire cast of Drawn To Life by @cirquedusoleil along with my artwork is a new core memory 🎪⭐️🎪 As an artist for Disney for almost 30 years and a HUGE fan of cirque who has also been a trapeze artist for 15 of those years, this show hits hard. I cried so many times tonight witnessing this incredible show from the front row. This surprise however just floored me. Thank you @bitsythings you are amazing. 💚❤️💙 And I finally got to meet @therealmisshesitation and @saulosarmiento 🙌🙌🙌 all such incredible performers and artists. I threw in a photo of my last trapeze performance just for fun. I wish I could run away with the circus. This was even better. Humbled and honored. #corememory #cirquedusoleil #drawntolife #disney

One. More. Time. 🎨⭐️🎨 Today is my last signing for Festival of the Arts. Find me from 11-1pm in the France Pavilion. Also the promised return of Atlantis and Treasure Planet. Fingers crossed. #artfulepcot

And that’s a wrap on Festival of the Arts at Epcot for me. 🎨⭐️🎨 Nine days of signing. My art will still be there unless it’s sold out. But if you don’t see what you’re looking for, make sure to ask a cast member. I can’t thank all the people that came out to support my art enough or those who stopped by just say hello. Also to all the amazing cast members that helped keep things running. I always love to visit with other incredible artists that keep me inspired @missmindyart @ashley24taylor @dylanbonner90 @ryanriller_ @fenwayweifan @joseytsao @jayratner81 @jmaruyama @yeseniadraws @anndanger and so many more. A lot of laughs and a lot of cosmos. The cast of Drawn to Life by @disney and @cirquedusoleil for welcoming me with open arms. I was so thrilled that I couldn’t sleep last night. With that note I’m going to nap, pack and head home in the morning. Til next time. ❤️🎨😊 #artfulepcot
